    <h2>Institutional Context</h2>
    <p>This research is conducted as a practice-based artistic PhD at the <strong>Universidad de Salamanca</strong>, one of Spain's oldest and most prestigious universities (founded 1218). The program privileges creative work as a primary mode of scholarly inquiry, alongside traditional written thesis work. The institutional support, interdisciplinary environment, and access to Europe's diverse musical and intellectual traditions have been invaluable to this project.</p>

    <p>The research builds on prior graduate study in the Erasmus Mundus program, which provided immersive engagement with European intellectual and artistic contexts across the UK, Spain, and Portugalā€”an experience that fundamentally shaped both the conceptual framework and the geographical orientation of the work.</p>
  
  
